  "prompt": "How do I recover a Yahoo hacked email address?",
  "response": "If your Yahoo email account has been hacked, it\u2019s important to act quickly to recover it. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you regain access to your account:\n\n### Step 1: Attempt to Sign In\n1. **Go to the Yahoo Sign-In Page**: Visit [Yahoo's sign-in page](https://login.yahoo.com).\n2. **Enter Your Email Address**: Input your email address and click \"Next.\"\n3. **Enter Your Password**: If you can sign in, change your password immediately.\n\n### Step 2: Use the Account Recovery Options\nIf you cannot sign in, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Click on \"Forgot Password?\"**: On the sign-in page, click on the \"Forgot password?\" link.\n2. **Follow the Prompts**: Enter your email address or mobile number associated with the account, then click \"Continue.\"\n3. **Select Recovery Method**: Yahoo will provide options to receive a recovery code via your registered phone number or an alternate email address. Choose one of these options and click \"Send Me a Code.\"\n4. **Enter the Verification Code**: Check your phone or alternate email for the verification code, enter it on Yahoo\u2019s website, and click \"Verify.\"\n\n### Step 3: Change Your Password\n1. **Set a New Password**: If verification is successful, you will be prompted to create a new password. Make sure it's strong and unique.\n2. **Sign In with Your New Password**: After changing the password, try signing in again with your updated credentials.\n\n### Step 4: Secure Your Account\n1. **Review Account Settings**: Once you're back in, check your account settings for any changes made by the hacker, like forwarding addresses or account recovery options.\n2. **Enable Two-Step Verification**: This adds an extra layer of security to your account. Go to the \"Account Security\" section and enable two-step verification for enhanced safety.\n3. **Check for Unauthorized Activity**: Look through your sent folder and inbox for any suspicious messages or changes you didn\u2019t make.\n\n### Step 5: Update Your Security Questions\n1. **Change Security Questions**: If you have security questions set up, update them to ensure that only you can access the account in the future.\n\n### Step 6: Scan for Malware\n1. **Run Antivirus Software**: Scan your devices (computers, smartphones, etc.) for malware or keyloggers that might have compromised your account.\n\n### Step 7: Contact Yahoo Support\nIf you are unable to recover your account using the steps above, you can contact Yahoo customer support for further assistance:\n- Go to the Yahoo Help page.\n- Use the \"Contact Us\" link for additional help.\n\n### Tips to Avoid Future Hacks\n- Use a strong and unique password for your Yahoo account.\n- Change your password regularly.\n- Enable two-factor authentication.\n- Be wary of phishing scams and suspicious links.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to recover your hacked Yahoo email account.",
